    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>The Ophiuchus cluster presents the nearest and best example of a cool core being disrupted by merger activity. Optical integral field spectroscopy has given us tantalising evidence that, having been divorced from its brightest cluster galaxy, the X-ray cool core of this galaxy cluster has continued to cool unchecked by regulation from AGN feedback. We propose to detect and trace cold molecular gas in the Ophiuchus cluster through ALMA band 6 CO (2-1) observations to confirm that a bona fide cooling flow is occurring and to probe the extent of this cooling.</prp:abstract>
